# How to Use

## Prerequisites

- **Autodesk Revit 2024** (or later)
- **pyRevit** installed and connected to Revit
  - Download: https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/releases

---

## Setup

### 1. Clone or Download this Repository

```
git clone https://github.com/wieglaf-folls/revit-tapered-beam-optimizer.git
```

Or download as ZIP and extract to any folder.

---

### 2. Load the Custom Family

1. Open your Revit project
2. Go to **Insert** tab → **Load Family**
3. Navigate to the `families/` folder in this repository
4. Select the `.rfa` file and click **Open**

> ⚠️ The script will not work correctly without the custom family loaded.

---

### 3. Run the Script via pyRevit

1. Open Revit with your project
2. Go to the **pyRevit** tab in the Revit ribbon
3. Click **pyRevit** → **Tools** → **Run Script**
4. Navigate to the `src/` folder and select the script
5. Click **Open** to execute

---

## Notes

- Make sure the tapered beam elements are already placed in the model before running the script
- The script processes all tapered beams in the active view
- Check the output log in the pyRevit console for any warnings or errors